3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=27|Home=23}}\n\n====Week 14: vs. Dallas Cowboys====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Green Bay Packers|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Fourteen: Dallas Cowboys at Green Bay Packers&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=December 13\n |time=3:25&nbsp;p.m. CST\n |road=Cowboys\n |R1=0|R2=0|R3=7|R4=0\n |home='''Packers'''\n |H1=0|H2=14|H3=0|H4=14\n |stadium=Lambeau Field, Green Bay, Wisconsin\n |attendance=78,369\n |weather={{convert|53|F|C}}, rain\n |referee=Brad Allen\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=Joe Buck, Troy Aikman and Erin Andrews\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2015121312/2015/REG14/cowboys@packers Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/56708/GB_Gamebook.pdf Gamebook]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n* No scoring plays\n'''Second quarter'''\n*GB \u2013 [[James Starks]] 13-yard pass from [[Aaron Rodgers]] ([[Mason Crosby]] kick), 9:55. ''Packers 7\u20130. '''Drive: 9 plays, 48 yards, 4:14.'''''\n*GB \u2013 [[Richard Rodgers (American football)|Richard Rodgers]] 3-yard pass from Aaron Rodgers (Mason Crosby kick), 2:45. ''Packers 14\u20130. '''Drive: 11 plays, 81 yards, 4:14.'''''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*DAL \u2013 [[Robert Turbin]] 7-yard run ([[Dan Bailey (American football)|Dan Bailey]] kick), 8:28. ''Packers 14\u20137. '''Drive: 4 plays, 80 yards, 2:07.'''''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n*GB \u2013 [[James Starks]] 30-yard run (Mason Crosby kick), 4:50. ''Packers 21\u20137. '''Drive: 12 plays, 84 yards, 6:34.'''''\n*GB \u2013 [[Eddie Lacy]] 1-yard run (Mason Crosby kick), 2:50. ''Packers 28\u20137. '''Drive: 4 plays, 38 yards, 0:25.'''''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n*DAL \u2013 [[Matt Cassel]] \u2013 13/29, 114 yards, INT\n*GB \u2013 [[Aaron Rodgers]] \u2013 22/35, 218 yards, 2 TD\n'''Top rushers'''\n*DAL \u2013 [[Darren McFadden]] \u2013 9 rushes, 111 yards\n*GB \u2013 [[Eddie Lacy]] \u2013 24 rushes, 124 yards, TD\n'''Top receivers'''\n*DAL \u2013 [[Jason Witten]] \u2013 5 receptions, 40 yards\n*GB \u2013 [[Randall Cobb (American football)|Randall Cobb]] \u2013 8 receptions, 81 yards\n'''Top tacklers'''\n*DAL \u2013 [[Barry Church]] \u2013 9 tackles, 2 assists\n*GB \u2013 [[Clay Matthews III]] \u2013 5 tackles, 1 assist (1 [[quarterback sack]])\n}}In a rematch of \"[[Dez Bryant]]'s no catch game\", the Packers rattled the depleted Cowboys 28\u20137. This was the first game Mike McCarthy took back play-calling duties after relinquishing it to Tom Clements.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mike McCarthy takes back Packers' playcalling duties|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000599611/article/mike-mccarthy-takes-back-packers-playcalling-duties|website=NFL.com|date=December 13, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Mike McCarthy calls plays for offense in win over Cowboys|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/14356004/mike-mccarthy-green-bay-packers-coach-reclaims-play-calling-responsibilities|website=[[ESPN.com]]|date=December 13, 2015}}</ref>\n\nWith the win, the Packers improved to 9\u20134.\n\n====Week 15: at Oakland Raiders====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Green Bay Packers|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Fifteen: Green Bay Packers at Oakland Raiders&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=December 20\n |time=3:05&nbsp;p.m. CST/1:05&nbsp;p.m. PST\n |road='''Packers'''\n |R1=14|R2=0|R3=10|R4=6\n |home=Raiders\n |H1=0|H2=13|H3=7|H4=0\n |stadium=[[O.co Coliseum]], [[Oakland, California]]\n |attendance=55,087\n |weather={{convert|54|F|C}}, cloudy\n |referee=Walt Anderson\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Chris Myers]], [[Ronde Barber]] and [[Jennifer Hale (sportscaster)|Jennifer Hale]]\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2015122009/2015/REG15/packers@raiders Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/56721/OAK_Gamebook.pdf Gamebook]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n* GB \u2013 [[John Kuhn]] 5-yard run, ([[Mason Crosby]] kick), 05:12. Drive: 4 plays, 17 yards, 01:1